##<a id='bbr-requirements'></a> BBR Requirements

`bbr` tool requires bosh credentials to connect to bosh and perform back up and restore of a deployment.

`BOSH-CLIENT-SECRET`: The value of `BOSH_CLIENT_SECRET` in the director tile under _Credentials_ > _Bosh Commandline Credentials_
`BOSH-TARGET`: The value of `BOSH_ENVIRONMENT` in the director tile under _Credentials_ > _Bosh Commandline Credentials_
`BOSH-CLIENT`: The value of `BOSH_CLIENT` in the director tile under _Credentials_ > _Bosh Commandline Credentials_
`PATH-TO-BOSH-CA-CERT`: Download Root CA certificate from _Opsmanager_ > _Settings_ > _Advanced_
`DEPLOYMENT-NAME`: Use the credentials to configure the `bosh` cli  and find the deployment that starts with `pivotal-container-service`

Note: `BOSH-TARGET` needs to be reachable from the machine you are running the `bbr` command.

